","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dpg7r","text":"Labeled 1.5 ml microfuge tubes with 600 μl isopropanol. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3u7et","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2giaq","text":"Part 1: COLLECTING THE MYCELIA","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":30}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"impb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"57cer","text":"If your mats are coming from a tube, vortex the tube quickly.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f38o8","text":"Using a sterile wooden stick (RNA-free cabinet), collect the mycelia from each tube and lay on a stack of paper towel (they will look like mycelia lollipops).Usually, 7 samples can fit on the length of a regular paper towel.Press with another layer of paper towel to get excess media off.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ahu5t","text":"Transfer each mycelia mat into the pre-labeled 1.5-ml tubes (set 1).","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bq767","text":"You can freeze them in -20oC or proceed to the extraction process.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":26,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"83mut","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cvtkp","text":"Part 2: DNA EXTRACTION","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":6},{"style":"bold","offset":8,"length":14}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2mvhj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1voaf","text":"Measure out the total amount of extraction buffer you need, and add Proteinase K (Freezer #4, tubes labeled PK).Each sample gets 500 μl extraction buffer with 3 μl Proteinase K.Just do the math for making a “master mix” depending on the # of samples you have.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7caqc","text":"Add ~500-503 μl of the buffer/Proteinase K mix to each sample.Vortex for 5 mins (using the vortex mixer with the round holder for multiple samples or the one which holds racks).Incubate the samples at 65oC for 1 hr (or more, not that critical).","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":203,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4hbsl","text":"Place tubes on ice, then add 200 μl of 7.5M ammonium acetate. Centrifuge at max speed for 5 min. * Tubes with chloroform go into the phenol/chloroform orange waste bucket next to chemical hood.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5l340","text":"While avoiding the interface, transfer ~500 μl of the supernatant into TUBE 3 (set with 600 μl isopropanol).Mix by inversion, then let sit for 10 min. Alternatively, can let sit at room temp. overnight for higher yield.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cbqaf","text":"Centrifuge at max speed for 10 min.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9b5mm","text":"Discard supernatant.Wash pellet with 70% ethanol. Centrifuge at max speed for 5 mins.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c6109","text":"Take out the ethanol. Air dry or speed vac.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9k7fq","text":"Suspend in 100 μl 1X TE with 1μl RNAse A (Freezer #4).Once again, you can make a “master mix” of TE buffer and RNase A depending on the number of your samples.Put in the 37oC water bath for 1 hr.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":172,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a73to","text":"Centrifuge at max speed for 1 min.
